.TH "of_reset_control_array_get" 9 "of_reset_control_array_get" "May 2021" "Kernel Hacker's Manual" LINUX
.SH NAME
of_reset_control_array_get \- Get a list of reset controls using device node.
.SH SYNOPSIS
.B "struct reset_control *" of_reset_control_array_get
.BI "(struct device_node *np "  ","
.BI "bool shared "  ","
.BI "bool optional "  ","
.BI "bool acquired "  ");"
.SH ARGUMENTS
.IP "np" 12
device node for the device that requests the reset controls array
.IP "shared" 12
whether reset controls are shared or not
.IP "optional" 12
whether it is optional to get the reset controls
.IP "acquired" 12
only one reset control may be acquired for a given controller
and ID
.SH "DESCRIPTION"
Returns pointer to allocated reset_control on success or error on failure
